devdoc.details: Smart contract for managing a benefactor's dead man's switch with assigned beneficiaries.

addBenefactorPublicKey(address,string).details: adds the benefactor public key to the specified benefactor-beneficiary pair

addBeneficiaries(address[]).details: Adds new beneficiaries to the list. Only callable by the benefactor.

params._beneficiaries: The addresses of the new beneficiaries.

addBeneficiaryPublicKey(address,address,.details: adds the beneficiary public key to the specified benefactor-beneficiary pair

checkAliveStatus(address).details: Checks the alive status of the benefactor.

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the benefactor is alive.

enableSwitch(address).details: Enables the dead man's switch. Only callable by beneficiaries.

getBenefactorPublicKey(address).details: returns the benefactor public key from the specified benefactor-beneficiary pair

getBeneficiaryData(address,address).details: Returns current status of benefactor to beneficiary.

getBeneficiaryPublicKey(address,address).details: returns the beneficiary public key from the specified benefactor-beneficiary pair

returns._0: The remaining countdown time in seconds.

isBeneficiary(address,address).details: Checks if the given address is a beneficiary. Only benefactor

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the address is a beneficiary.

removeBenefactor(address).details: Removes a benefactor. Only callable by benefactor.

removeBeneficiary(address).details: Removes a beneficiary from the list. Only callable by the benefactor.

params._beneficiary: The address of the beneficiary to be removed.

removeIpfsCID(address,string).details: Removes an IPFS CID from the specified beneficiary. Only callable by benefactor.

respondToSwitch().details: Performs actions based on benefactor's activity when responding to an enabled switch. Only callable by the benefactor.

setBenefactor().details: Sets up a benefactor. Only callable by benefactor.
